baseline.comment:
1.  Central Electoral Commission does not have a gender policy and does not consider the gender element of electoral policy and planning. Limited collection of sex disaggregated data; 
2. There is little or no consideration of human rights and gender issues in electoral management and processes 
3. Lack of necessary capacity to enforce and implement the Central Electoral Commission institutional development plan; 
4. No staff have formal Personal Development Plans; 
5. Insufficient capacity at  Central Electoral Commission  to perform effectively policy and legal research functions;
 6. Relationships between  Central Electoral Commission , Parliament and key Government ministries dysfunctional and not institutionalized; 
7. Percentage of voters on supplementary lists - 6.25% at 2010 parliamentary elections; 
8. Electronic Voters’ register absent.

actual.comment:
1. More than 100 requests for information on biomass benefits and use were received
2. 620 families have biomass boilers installed as a result of the subsidy scheme implementation, being refunded the amount of EUR 1,300; 
3. The co-generation plant is fully functional. A study on the replication potential of co-generation technologies in Moldova was developed 
4. The PPP was initiated and biomass heating plants have been installed in 21 public institutions from Leova District and the power is supplied by an economic entity; 
5. 100 new jobs were created.

target.comment:
1. 10 training modules of the Center for Continuous Electoral Training for 2014 parliamentary elections gender mainstreamed;
2. 40%  women as Heads of electoral commissions at district level
3. At least 3 targeted voter education campaigns with focus on women, youth, and minorities conducted prior to 2014 Parliamentary elections
4.  At least 50 vulnerable women supported by the project to formulate their needs and issues to be raised in meetings with MPs to be organised in 2015;
5.  Activity to start in 2015

actual.comment:
1. Achieved. 10 training modules of the Center for Continuous Electoral Training gender aligned;  
2. Partially achieved.  38% women elected in leadership positions of district electoral commissions in 2014 parliamentary elections 
3. Achieved. 5 targeted voter education campaigns reaching out to 431, 280 persons, including ethnic minority women, women with disabilities, and first-time voters from 11 towns and 13 Roma communities conducted;
4. 66 women from vulnerable groups supported by the project formulated their needs to be addressed  in meetings with MPs scheduled for 2015;
5.  Activity to start in 2015

target.comment:
1. 4 training modules of CCET for  2015 local elections gender mainstreamed;
2. At least 40% women in leadership positions of district electoral commissions in 2015 local elections  
3.At least  2 voter education campaigns targeting specific groups of voters (women from vulnerable groups, Roma, other ethnic minority women) conducted prior to 2015 local elections;
4. At least 4 regional parliamentary forums bringing constituents from vulnerable groups, particularly women, and MPs facilitated;  
5. Capacities of all 11 newly elected women MPs enhanced through training in the areas of strategic political communications, media skills and public image
